.TH "ti_sci_cmd_idle_device_exclusive" 9 "ti_sci_cmd_idle_device_exclusive" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_sci_cmd_idle_device_exclusive \- Command to idle a device managed by TISCI that is exclusively owned by requesting host.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ti_sci_cmd_idle_device_exclusive
.BI "(const struct ti_sci_handle *handle "  ","
.BI "u32 id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
Pointer to TISCI handle as retrieved by *ti_sci_get_handle
.IP "id" 12
Device Identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Request for the device - NOTE: the client MUST maintain integrity of
usage count by balancing get_device with put_device. No refcounting is
managed by driver for that purpose.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if all went fine, else return appropriate error.
